headline: Caleres Q3 profit plunges on margin pressure
summary: American footwear company Caleres has reported higher third-quarter (Q3) sales but a steep drop in profitability, as margin pressure, higher operating expenses and dilution from its Stuart Weitzman acquisition offset strength in its core brands.

headline: 1 Volatile Stock to Keep an Eye On and 2 We Turn Down
summary: Market swings can be tough to stomach, and volatile stocks often experience exaggerated moves in both directions. While many thrive during risk-on environments, many also struggle to maintain investor confidence when the ride gets bumpy.
